column28:
Proposal: "Oxford Text Archive, https://ota.bodleian.ox.ac.uk/ (209 novels, 350 plays, 64 collections of poetry; most in TEI)"
Homepage: "A repository of full-text literary and linguistic resources. Thousands of texts in more than 25 languages."; "The Oxford Text Archive (OTA) is a repository of digital literary and linguistic resources for research and teaching. The OTA was created at and remains a part of the University of Oxford. We also offer advice to resource creators about best practice for creating digital resources, and to users of digital resources on how to benefit from existing resources."
Commentary: founded by Lou Burnard & Susan Hockey; currently under review (nov2021); they provide single entries in DC, via OAI-PMH, use CMDI, BIBTEX, handles, support open data (but also support restricted access data); clear info on licenses; The OTA is a registered CLARIN C Centre, and the repository is based on the CLARIN DSpace platform;
OTA collections can be found via the VLO; records are displayed with their metadata and download possiblilities (HTML, TEI, epub, ?);
